item.title: HELP Cmd prompt - broke. Can't run servers.. [PICS]
item.dc:creator: @X-J-K-X X-J-K-X
item.description:
@X-J-K-X wrote:

Start > Control Panel > Performance And Maintenance > System > Advanced > Environmental Variables…

Okay now, find one called class path. Replace it with this

CLASSPATH=C:\Prgram Files\Java\jdk1.6.0\bin;%CLASSPTH%;

Hit ok.

Next find Path, replace it with this

%SystemRoot%\system32;%SystemRoot%;%SystemRoot%\System32\Wbem;C:\Program Files\QuickTime\QTSystem\

This will allow you to run your server + Use CMD prompt like normal. H2H.

P.S - Change the Java, to your java type.

Too late but hay.
